## 3. Final Determination

**【Breakthrough Level】**

**Reasoning:** This work breaks the industrial dogma that "RMP inevitably degrades confinement" and "gas injection is merely passive relief." By implementing a composite strategy of **"magnetic peak-shaving + ultrasonic beam-induced high-frequency dissipation,"** we provide the first engineering roadmap for the deterministic transition of Type-I ELMs to the Grassy regime. It requires no novel PFC materials or new heating systems; instead, it leverages existing hardware synergy to convert catastrophic transient heat loads into manageable steady-state heat flux, solving the fundamental deadlock of "survivability" for fusion reactors.

